observations.recommendation:
a. For the Local Chief Executive to institutionalize the creation of Inventory Committee, its proper documentation and assignment of personnel to conduct annual physical inventory/inventory taking of its Property, Plant and Equipment;
b. For the General Service Office to promptly prepare and submit the Correct Report on Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment to the Municipal Accountant and the Audit Team for validation;
c. For the General Service Office and the Municipal Accounting Office to prepare annual reconciliation of the RPCPPE as actually counted with the accounting records to establish the correct value of PPE at year end;
d. For the Municipal Accounting Office to obtain necessary data from Municipal Engineering Office, then prepare and maintain subsidiary ledger cards for Local Road Network, provide depreciation separately to each component of the road network, submit a lapsing schedule for the computation of depreciation, and disclose the road network system in the Notes to Financial Statements in accordance with the prescribed format under COA Circular No. 2015-008;
e. For the Municipal Accountant to secure supporting documents and draw the necessary adjustments in the books to reflect recognition of depreciation expenses and adjustments to all the affected accounts. Henceforth, properly recognize annual depreciation of Property, Plant and Equipment based on the guidelines set under IPSAS 17 and other relevant COA issuances; and
f. For the management to revisit the provisions of IPSAS 17 on the required disclosures for each class of property, plant and equipment recognized in the financial statements and properly reflect the same on the Notes to Financial Statements.

a. For the Municipal Accountant to review and analyze the idle/long-outstanding balances of Due to Other NGAs accounts. Make a representation letter for confirmation to the source agencies for the unliquidated balances for proper reconciliation and adjustments in the books if warranted and/or immediate liquidation;
b. For the Accounting Office to maintain and update constantly the Subsidiary Ledgers pursuant to COA Circular 2020-004, wherein the Local Government Units should use the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs prescribing the adaptation of IPSAS;
c. For the Municipal Accounting Office to ensure the completeness and propriety of the supporting documents to be attached in the disbursement vouchers upon submission;
d. For the Municipal Engineering Office to revisit the provisions under the Annex “E” of the 2016 IRR of RA 9184 and ensure that approval on the contract time extension is properly done and documented;
e. For the BAC together with the General Service Office to ensure clarity in the contracts between the Supplier and LGU and prescribed forms are properly filled out.

We recommend the following:
a. Make representations with the bank officials to finally determine the status of the bank balance appearing in the LGU books. Prepare the necessary adjusting entries to reflect the correct cash balance based on the result of the representation made;
b. Direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit the complete bank reconciliation statements for all depository accounts. Likewise, all should be submitted as at year-end.

We recommended the following:
a. Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the inventory;
b. Determine and dispose all obsolete and unserviceable properties in accordance with the guidelines;
c. Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.

We recommended and management agreed to the following:
a. Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the mandatory physical inventory;
b. Require the MAO and GSO to maintain sufficient property ledger cards and property stock cards, respectively, as MAO; control records to facilitate the regular reconciliation of records with MAO;
c. Determine and dispose all obsolete and unserviceable properties in accordance with the guidelines;
d. Provide depreciation for the Land Improvements and Infrastructure Assets; and
e. Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.

Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the mandatory physical inventory;
Create an inventory team to conduct a complete physical count / inventory of all properties in accordance with existing regulations and in order to establish the actual existence;
Submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the latter's ledger cards and furnish the same Report to the Office of the Auditor;
Require the Accounting and GSO to maintain ledger and property / stock cards as control records to facilitate the regular reconciliation of records; and
Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.

We recommended and management agreed to the following:
Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the mandatory physical inventory;
Submit a complete Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the latter's ledger cards;
Require the MAO and GSO to maintain ledger cards and property cards, respectively, as control records to facilitate the regular reconciliation of records with MAO; and
Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.
